input: [int | uint | buff | string-ascii | string-utf8], [int | uint | buff | string-ascii | string-utf8]
description: Compares two inputs (Inputs must be of the same type), returns true if INPUT-1 is greater than or equal to INPUT-2 and false otherwise.
Starting with Stacks 1.0, the >=-comparable types are int and uint.
Starting with Stacks 2.1, the >=-comparable types are expanded to include string-ascii, string-utf8 and buff.
